Description.LocalizedString: She'd given so much to help others; all she wanted was someone to comfort her. But no one did.
She seemed forsaken and forlorn, looking at the world with hopeless, sullen eyes.
The blonde-haired cop was a welcome sight in The Fog. She had gentle eyes beneath her tough exterior, the kind you can immediately trust.
Sullen, he travels to the remote town of Silent Hill, to their “special place”.
She stays one step ahead of danger with these sensitive antennae.
Preferring her bold look, she owned this new, playful side of hers.
Preferring her bold look, she owned this new, playful side of hers.
She was still alive, but with wounds that won't heal…
Her grief resonated with the memory, finding a bit of solace in company.
The dark pants given to officers of the Brahm’s police department. Sadly, the holster is empty.
A comfortable pair of loose-fitting jeans with black leather shoes.
This flared footwear may look more fashionable than functional, but many foes failed to finish her when she fought in these.
A pair of sturdy denims with a spiked belt that displayed her edgy side.
A pair of sturdy denims with a spiked belt that displayed her edgy side.
She pounded on the door, begged him not to leave. She didn't want to be alone again, not like this.
She felt like there was no escape; her life was trapped in the four walls of a suffocating school.
The uniform given to officers of the Brahm’s police department. The gold emblem carries a tone of authority.
Robbie the Rabbit provides some lightheartedness to the ominous symbol emblazoned on the front.
A warm, sturdy coat to face the haunting mist of Silent Hill.
The costume she wore while moonlighting as a romantic crimefighter.
Versatile shirt that allowed her to fight and live another day.
